Patch Set 4:

Are these migration scripts universally compatible with sqlalchemy or specifically with MySQL and Postgres? If we leave these checks in place, yes we will break everyone not using MySQL do we silently break all tohse people if we just remove the checks?

Patch Set 4:

> Are these migration scripts universally compatible with sqlalchemy
 > or specifically with MySQL and Postgres? If we leave these checks
 > in place, yes we will break everyone not using MySQL do we silently
 > break all tohse people if we just remove the checks?

Hey, yes those scripts are compatible with MySQL and postgres except syntax of triggers, and that's the only reason glance is not supporting postgres for online upgrades. Other than that there is no issue with the scripts.

Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

We should not remove the engine validations, specially from the individual actions where we would ending up to point that if admin ran expand command agains postgre db engine we actually have the DB barfing on us when the triggers are tried to be applied instead of us telling the admin that this can't be done as your db is not supported.

It's fine to limit the triggers to those individual commands only and leave the checks out of db_sync, but we need to be really clear documenting that being the case specially now after we merged the statement that we use E-M-C everywhere in our db migrations.
